Cheers y’all 🥂 #2023

This lady just earned her Associates Degree in Communications and graduated with honors ;) I have also been accepted to Cal State Fullerton where I will be working towards my bachelor’s degree. Whoo Hoo! Go Titans! My biggest goal was to inspire my kids to go to college and I succeeded! My baby girl now has her eyes on the prize and so does my son ;) So many times on this journey I kicked myself in the a** for not going back sooner, however I  stopped and checked myself. I’m exactly where I was meant to be. Had things been different I wouldn’t have experienced all the amazing projects I’ve been involved in with my career . I thought about the life I have and I don’t regret doing things my own way . For some , a straight focused path is for them , for this crazy lady , a zig zag , loopty loop , roller coaster is the path I chose and wow, it has been an epic ride . When I reminisce on all that I have accomplished in my career and in life I just think wow I have come so far . I’ll watch TV and see all the talent that I have worked on or walk into a store and see advertisements with models I have worked on and think of all the beautiful places I have seen because of my career . I never thought I would achieve the things that I have working as an artist . I have really come a long way from the hot mess I was when I was young , but the great about hitting rock bottom at 19-21 years old was there was only one way to go , up ⬆️ .  In other words I’m so f*cking proud of myself . Thank you to
God for the strength to pursue this journey , to my honey who has always had my back and for helping me with my math homework you have been my rock and a huge inspiration to me . Also thank you to my kiddos for being understanding when I was trying to balance everything out . You kids motivate me to be the strongest woman I can be and I love you all so much . Lastly thank you to some of my friends and family for your encouragement during this journey I appreciate you more than you will ever know , you know who you are . ❤️🙏🏽😘 #neverstopgrowing

Our future is bright ✨✨✨
.

social_posts.post_text: Thank you to everyone who made my birthday so special. Every year I like to reflect on my life . I am beyond grateful . I never pictured my life to be what it is today . I’m happy and living my life the way I want to live it . I have traveled to some of the most amazing places in the world , have worked with and on such amazing talented and interesting people , I have seen so many amazing bands and musicians live, I have peed myself laughing at countless comedy shows , visited epic museums,  have shared cries and laughs with amazing friends and family . I have a really cute home that we worked hard for and I love coming home to . But most importantly I have thee most beautiful children who I love so much and an amazing husband who I love , adore, and still crush on. I have so much to be grateful for . None of this was handed to me it came from hard work . Behind the scenes of the “perfect instagram post” there has been heart break , addiction at a very young age , depression, ptsd , anxiety , childhood trauma , extreme fatigue and exhaustion from just going going going and never stopping . But with God , hard work, determination, and strong support system I overcame a lot . Strong Relationships, love , family , life, it all takes hard work, and to this day I still work hard to be a woman that my kids look up to. Am I rich ? No. but I live a rich life and that means something different to everybody. But to me having a strong family and coming home to peace, love and appreciation is just everything. Setting a goal and crushing it, picking a place I want to travel to saving my $$ to make that happen gives me great satisfaction. To me , that is truly a rich life. As I sit back and look around I’m just so proud of myself for constantly trying to better myself and push myself to do the things that scare me most and be the best human I can .

Thank you all who attended the Mejia Birthday/Graduation party !!! 🥳🥂❤️ It meant the world to my kids and I , we definitely felt the love and appreciate all the beautiful cards filled with words of love and encouragement, and on top of that , thank you for all your generosity. We haven’t seen everyone in such a long time , though we tried to make our rounds , it was tricky and wish I had more time to spend with each of you. I love you all so much .

 Special thank you to all the godparents @rtd011 for your help setting up , emotional support , and the best cake ever , so bomb ! @mrs.nat562 my seester for your love and for the aqua frescas. @mrs.isita for the bomb elote set up and helping me chill after a crazy week . @manriquezsteve for the bomb pineapple piñata , candy , and bags lol. @anthonyducoulombier and @evmduco for the bionicos and the awesome Cal state Fullerton merch ! Heck yeah ! Go Tuffy ! I love , appreciate, and value you all so much , you have no idea . 

We did what we could with our short time frame and budget, the kids Moe and I really worked as a team and made it happen . We hope you all had fun and enjoyed making memories with all of us , we will never forget it !!!

Also I could only tag 20 peeps sorry if I didn’t tag you all . 😘❤️🙏🏽🥳🥂🤘🏽🫶🎶✌🏽🥰

Our cruise to Mexico was amazing! My babies had a great time and the hubby and I did too . We zip lined for the first time and it was awesome ! I can’t wait to zip line again!!! @royalcaribbean was a beautiful ship with lots of beautiful artwork everywhere 😍 and many family friendly activities, we particularly liked ice skating and dancing at the silent disco . My son loved playing pool with his dad , going down the water slide , and rock climbing. My hubby loved hitting the craps tables and our daughter loved relaxing , tanning and sneaking off for pizza . Tequila tasting in Mazatlan was awesome but Puerto Vallarta was my favorite the water was so warm and so were the people 😍 I can’t wait to go back!

A little tip , if you are hired for wet hairstyling your rate stays the same !!! Wet hairstyling may be simple , but it’s not ! 

1. You need to ensure it isn’t completely dripping and it can’t be too dry or it looks frizzy.

2. Depending on the look it needs to be combed down smooth to the head or have movement .

3. Hairs need to be placed on body and face strategically or it can ruin makeup . 

Basically it’s a lot of work so don’t sell yourself short ;)

Our return visit to Paris was short , sweet, and hot 🥵 🔥 We thought by traveling in fall the weather would be cool, guess not 😒. Though it was hotter than heck we were able to do the things we couldn’t do the first time like getting our portrait painted by an artist, and taking the Seine river cruise and visiting the Amelie Cafe 😍. Probably the most special of all was  visiting our friend @united_states_of_chris . This man put us up in his apartment for 9 days 12 years ago and was a complete gentleman and I am so proud of him and I hope we continue to keep in touch . Ugh I swear i want to go back already even if it’s just to stuff my face for the weekend lol 🐽🐷 Everything is so good . On the last day I was so sad but excited for the adventure ahead , up next Belgium 🇧🇪 
.

Brussels Belgium 🇧🇪 😍🙌🏽❤️🍻🍫🧇

Whilst looking at our train route to Amsterdam we noticed that Belgium was on the way … so we figured why not 🤷🏽‍♀️ We had heard great things and decided to see what was up . I’m so glad we did ! The waffles , chocolate, and beer , was so bomb!!!! In total I believe we tried over 30 beers 😬 Not to mention the people were super kind. The Grand Place was one of the most impressive squares we have ever been too in all of Europe the  grandeur of it all was simply incredible, we also happened to arrive when this awesome percussion ensemble was playing Coldplay 😍. Don’t skip on Belgium when in Europe ! 
.
#belgium🇧🇪 #travel #explore #bespontaneous #mannequinpis #belgiumbeer #begiumchocolate #belgiumwaffles #live #gratefulforlife #theebeautyheroine

Bruges Belgium 🇧🇪 
.
This town felt unreal , out of a storybook . We were lucky enough to grab a table at a local cafe just as the rain started 😍🌧️ and it made the city glisten . This medieval town has been so well kept you really got a glimpse of what life was like in the 12th century. A warning to you light weights the beer is strong!!! I had two and felt tipsy and the narrow stairs in Belgium were a bit of a challenge but I made it 💪🏽😂🥴. Bruges is a must see and even if your not a beer drinker…this is the time to drink up… too good not to try !!!! I recommend La Chouffe my new favorite;) 
.
#bruges🇧🇪 #flemish #beer #lachouffe #traveloften #live #gratefuleveryday #explore #whereintheworldismichelleandmoses #theebeautyheroine

The 5am call times , lugging around 70+ lbs of equipment, not eating , too much coffee, not enough coffee , no breaks , and people constantly judging your work . With all that being said my job is amazing when you meet and work on people like @hyperactiveblonde . This group of women have been one of the kindest , understanding, and caring people I have ever worked with . They made me rest, eat , and made sure I had coffee. I appreciate them so much and it made the time it took to complete 10 services fly by . Thankful for beautiful people like them . Wishing them all the love and happiness in the world 🌎

Amsterdam we’ll be back ! Up next Germany 🇩🇪 

Pic 2 - Theater Tuschinski built in 1919 is one of the most gorgeous art deco style theaters ever 😍. Day 1 I thought it was abandoned. Day 2 curiosity got the best of me and I tried shaking all the doors and it opened . So the hubs and I watched the new Indiana Jones . This theater is gorgeous and the seats were all red velvet mini love seats . Stay curious ;) 

Pic 3 - Anne Frank House 🙏🏽🥺 it was closed on this day , but I can’t believe I was here. Something to remember, be respectful , too many tourists acting like imbeciles in this area . 🙄

Pic 4- Is a reminder to always get lost ;) because you’ll never know what amazing things you’ll be able to see along the way . 

Pic 5- This is going to sound cheesy but ever since I was little and watched Pinocchio , I wanted wooden shoes . I looked all over for them and all I found was slippers , I talked to a few people and found that I need to order them , however I walked into this store and there was these humongous klompen. It really made my day !

Pic 6-We stumbled into this karaoke 🎤 bar and everyone was so friendly. These young kids were so fun and were belting out Abba hits at the top of their lungs . The bartenders were extremely welcoming and we loved this spot !

Rothenburg ob der Tauber Germany 🇩🇪 😍

This town still has thee original city wall which we walked a mile of . The food was delicious, the toy window displays were so magical , and the people in Germany were very polite and kind to us .

Cologne Germany 🇩🇪 
.
The Cologne Cathedral was truly a site to see! The largest gothic church in Northern Europe and is known to carry the relics of the three wiseman , crazy right ?! This journey was tough as our original train was cancelled .So we, along with 100 other passengers , had to squeeze onto another train and just hope for a decent spot . We were lucky and found something . The next morning we would once again have our train cancelled and would run our a**es off to multiple platforms to find our new train,m. It was hectic , we were sweaty , and it took a good 30 min for my heart rate to go back down and catch my breath as we were both lugging 60lb luggage bags. 😅 Riding trains throughout Europe provided us to be able to see a lot more and bypass the checking in and security checks at airports. But the last minute cancellations and platform changes were a bit stressful. Thankful to my husband for handling the trains like a boss ! 
.

Munich & Thee official Oktoberfest ❤️🇩🇪🙏🏽🙌🏽🍻
.
Wow! Munich was absolutely amazing ! There had been people who said they were treated poorly in this country and we shouldn’t go there, but we never once experienced that . There were so many people who went out of their way to treat us with kindness and patience. I do wish we would have had time to visit Hamburg and Berlin … but I know we will be back because Oktoberfest was so fun . Originally when we had first planned this trip we were going to do the full 2 weeks in Germany and really explore the country but with Europe being so small and the trains being pretty convenient to the surrounding countries we decided to switch things up a bit . I think adding two days to this trip would have been perfect as we were cheated a day because of Turkish Airlines 😡. Oktoberfest kicked my butt and I was a zombie the next day lol. I have never in my life drank so much beer as I did on this trip and I need to work off my little belly lol . If anyone is ever headed over to Germany or any places we have visited and wants some tips hit me up . I loved all of our hotels and found such good restaurants. Ugh I already miss it . Prost 🍻 Y’all ! Happy New Year! Be adventurous, explore, and create beautiful memories.
